{
  "text": "Combined with infinite loops and if statements, blocks and exits suffice to express efficiently all reducible control-flow graphs, notably those arising from C loops. The C statements break and continue are translated as appropriate exit statements. Blazy et al. [CITATION_1] detail the translation of these C statements into Cminor.",
